<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 6:24PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN ANSON...
SOUTHEASTERN MONTGOMERY AND RICHMOND COUNTIES THROUGH 730 PM EST...
At 624 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadesboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Hoffman, Ellerbe, Lilesville, Morven,
Norman, McFarlan, and Diggs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
